result.execSummary:
The defendant Connor J Jung was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property >$10,000 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime, Penalty - Theft >$10,000], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Court has set a Probation Review Hearing for 2/08/16 at 3:00 PM.

miscConds.notes: $2,982 of restitution is to be paid to the victim, Donald Gospodarek first before payments are made to Wisconsin Mutual Insurance Co. Defendant to pay any statutorily authorized surcharges.

To pay the costs of the action.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. To pay supervision fees as ordered by the Dept. of Corrections.

Maintain full-time employment and/or schooling. Graduate from high school.
9/22/15 - Court will allow defendant to obtain a GED/HSED in place of graduating from high school.
No contact with the victim, other than the apology letter. No contact with co-defendant, J.S.

Complete any counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments as appropriate resulting from the Department's COMPAS assessment. Write a minimum 100 word apology letter to victim on why he did what he did. This to be done within the first 30 days of probation. Defendant can petiton for early termination of probation after 3 years upon successful completion of all conditions of probation and with recommendation from Dept. of Corrections.

timeConds.notes: 60 days stayed. To be used at the Court's discretion by petition from probation agent. Huber release granted. 60 days to report.
Stayed as long as defendant is in school full-time and/or working full-time.

supervisions.notes: Huber release and good time granted. Credit for time served.
To pay the costs of the action. 60 days to pay or set up payment plan with the Clerk of Courts office.
Restitution owing converted to a civil judgment.
